OL,2,MSo you want to go to space?
OL,4,CEmily Selwood
OL,5,CSat 14:50-15:10
OL,6,CStage B
OL,8,GThis humorous talk, needing no prior
OL,9,Gknowledge of rocketry or space travel,
OL,10,Gwill take a walk through different
OL,11,Gways humans have considered getting to
OL,12,Gspace. From things that actually work,
OL,13,Gto the things that could theoretically
OL,14,Gwork if you ignore things like safety
OL,15,Gor the rest of humanity, via things
OL,16,Gthat should work but only on other
OL,17,Gcelestial objects. With pictures,
OL,18,Gdiagrams, and increasingly abstract
OL,19,Gsketches. While some of the ideas may
OL,20,Gseem a quite sci-fi this will only
OL,22,D]CEMFFAX: The world at your fingertips\
